The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

LO-CAL

Derek O'Brien 

 Dalhousie Square (correctly Benoy Badal Dinesh Bag) has been listed by the World Monument Fund among the 100 most endangered heritage sites in the world. The good news is that funds are being pumped in for the repair and restoration of buildings around the 2 sq km area which, till 1911, was the political, financial and social capital of the British Empire. So let?s be optimistic about the initiative, however small, and drown all cynicism in the waters of the Hooghly 

 QUESTIONS

 Histori-Cal 

 1. Which Bengali physician and politician was born on July 1, 1882 and passed away on July 1, 1962? 2. Which famous Bengali is noted for his defence of Aurobindo Ghosh in a famous early-20th century trial? 3. Which historical character is the subject of investigation of the one-man Justice M.K. Mukherjee Commission?

 Academi-Cal

 4. In Calcutta, which educational institution would you find at 1, Khudiram Bose Sarani? 5. Which organisation did Dr Mahendra Lal Sircar set up in July 1876 at 210, Bowbazar Street and which now operates out of its premises adjacent to Jadavpur University? 6. Besides the main campus, where would you find a reading room of the National Library that stores newspapers? 

 TOpI-cal 

 Medi-Cal 

 The Calcutta Police Hospital was set up in 1897 in Amherst Street for the treatment of the city?s police personnel. In 1921, the institution moved to its present location in Bhowanipore. Situated at 2, Beninandan Street, the hospital today has 300 beds. 

 ANSWERS 

 1. Bidhan Chandra Roy; 2. CR Das; 3. Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose; 4. RG Kar Medical College; 5. Indian Association for the Cultivation of Science; 6. Esplanade, at 6, Esplanade East 




